This file summarizes changes made between Object Professional versions 1.20
and 1.21. It is of interest primarily to Fast Update Plan subscribers.

Bugs fixed
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPCRT
  - Corrected problem with CRT/OPCRT conflict check in DLLs

OPCTRL
  - Fixed problem with ChangeHidden and pushbuttons
  - Fixed problem with clusters and dcSelectLocally option

OPDIALOG
  - Could not add right-aligned prompt containing '&'

OPDIR
  - Could display more than one column in PathList

OPDOS
  - GetDiskClass returned SubstDrive for invalid drives
  - GetDiskClass returned bogus results in an OS/2 DOS box
  - ShellWithPrompt gave -7 error in pmode
  - Disk label routines and SetDta died in pmode
  - FileHandlesOpen produced GPFs in pmode
  - PRINT.COM services produced GPFs in pmode
  - Potential for problems in pmode with SetRawMode
  - Master environment code didn't work under DRDOS

OPDRAG
  - Improved drag move/resize behavior

OPENHKBD
  - Int 16 handler was messed up in 1.20

OPEXEC
  - Updated GetDiskClass to match version in OPDOS

OPFORM
  - Fixed read error problem when loading forms that use HP printers
  - Not disposing printer allocated by form loaded from a stream
  - Margin settings were handled improperly

OPHELP
  - Shift-Tab command missed cross-references

OPINLINE
  - Reboot macro didn't work in PMode

OPINT
  - Using EmulateInt could lead to random behavior/hangs

OPMENU
  - Couldn't drag highlight on items with submenus
  - Alpha searching was incomplete with protected items

OPROOT
  - PointerStack crashed if more than 16380 elements pushed
  - LargeBitSet.PrevSet skipped set bits

OPSTRING
  - BMSearchUC locked up occasionally

OPSWAP1
  - ModuleInstalled and ModulePtrByName failed with MemoryMate

OPTSR
  - ModuleInstalled and ModulePtrByName failed with MemoryMate

MAKEHELP
  - Empty last topic caused problems in OPHELP; MH now prevents this

POPHELP
  - POPHELP was permanently grabbing COM2 under OS/2

TPUI
  - Would not compile in protected mode application


New Features
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Most new features are described in detail in READ.1ST. The following
is a brief description of them, arranged by unit. Minor enhancements
to existing programs and routines are listed here only and are denoted
by asterisks.

OPCRT
  - Reenabled UseCRT define and CRT conflict checking in pmode

OPCTRL
  - dcSelectLocally option now affects drawing of cluster items

OPDEVICE
  - Added registration routines for Brother M-1709 and IBM QuickWriter

OPDIALOG
  * Added support for efReadOnly option for edit controls
  - Added Enter-To-Tab option

OPENTRY
  * Better error when no mask passed to AddXxxField call

OPERRHAN
  * Made changes to allow unit to link with SB Pascal+ 6.14
  * Added support for runtime error 215 (arithmetic overflow)

OPINLINE
  - Added LoNibble, HiNibble, and MakeByte routines

OPMENU
  - Added option to keep the select char visible in a highlighted item

OPMOUSE
  * Protect against bogus MouseMove events in Windows DOS box

OPROOT
  - Now allows more than 64K elements in a linked list
  - Unit may now be overlayed

OPSTRING
  * Made Form and LongIntForm mutually reentrant
  - Str2Int/Str2Word/Str2Long now recognize 0000h and 0x0000 formats
